OL,3,CTeenager recalls moments before school
OL,4,Cbus burst into flames
OL,6,FHe said: "Tyler's mentioned a number
OL,7,Fof times that the bus is not up to
OL,8,Fstandard. It's breaking down. Things
OL,9,Fare breaking on the bus all the time."
OL,11,FAsked whether he thought the school or
OL,12,Fthe council were aware of concerns, he
OL,13,Fsaid: "What I would have hoped (is)
OL,14,Fthat whoever got the service provider
OL,15,Fon board would have had risk
OL,16,Fassessments.
OL,18,F"And I'm hoping the bus company (has)
OL,19,Fgot a strong maintenance record for
OL,20,Fthis bus as well.
